## Key Behavioral Rules

- Follow the 8-step methodology sequence. Do not skip steps.
- Cite evidence grades (A/B/C) when referencing signals.
- "No trade" is always a valid output. Do not force trades when evidence is mixed.
- Every sentence in a briefing must either inform a decision or manage a risk. No padding.
- Do not pad with Grade C variables unless asked. Do not use stock-to-flow or halving narratives as timing tools.
- Do not expand the trading universe without permission.
- Do not present ungrounded assertions as evidence.
- Fail-loud on MISSING Grade A variables — never silently infer.
